      "text": "The success of this model of bureaucracy [⇒ [[Max Weber’s Bureaucracy Model]]] can best be explained historically. It opposes arbitrariness at all levels of order, it concentrates arbitrariness at the top, which is then assumed to be disciplined by its own value relationships and environmental conditions – in the economy by the market and in public administration by politics bound by the rule of law."
